### Tested versions

- Reproducable in: v4.4.1.stable.mono.official [49a5bc7b6]
- Reproducable in: v4.5.beta.mono.custom_build [27ac237c0] (doubt it's different on master; no changes to module)

### System information

Godot v4.5.beta.mono (27ac237c0) - Windows 11 (build 26100) - Multi-window, 2 monitors - Vulkan (Forward+) - dedicated NVIDIA GeForce GTX 1080 (NVIDIA; 32.0.15.6636) - Intel(R) Core(TM) i5-14500 (20 threads) - 31.77 GiB memory

### Issue description

Receive following error when attempting to run scene.

<img width="1158" height="51" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/810da54b-1755-42d0-b9e8-e90f499ee4f5" />

### Steps to reproduce

```C#
using Godot;
using System;

public partial class CSScript : Node
{
	public CSScript(int optional_param = 4)
	{
		GD.Print(optional_param);
	}
}
```

1. Use above code or MRP.
2. Run scene with script attached to node.

### Minimal reproduction project (MRP)

[cs-default-constructor-mrp.zip](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/21546979/cs-default-constructor-mrp.zip)

### Tested versions

- Reproducable in: v4.4.1.stable.mono.official [49a5bc7b6]
- Reproducable in: v4.5.beta.mono.custom_build [27ac237c0] (doubt it's different on master; no changes to module)

### System information

Godot v4.5.beta.mono (27ac237c0) - Windows 11 (build 26100) - Multi-window, 2 monitors - Vulkan (Forward+) - dedicated NVIDIA GeForce GTX 1080 (NVIDIA; 32.0.15.6636) - Intel(R) Core(TM) i5-14500 (20 threads) - 31.77 GiB memory

### Issue description

Seems that GDScript is not aware of of C# constructor function signature and so cannot construct script objects defined in C#.

```gdscript
extends Node

const CSScript = preload("res://CSScript.cs")

func _ready():
	add_child(CSScript.new(2))
```

```C#
using Godot;
using System;

public partial class CSScript : Node
{
	public CSScript(int req_param)
	{
		GD.Print(req_param);
	}
}
```

Error is message is:

<img width="798" height="50" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/bc5160c2-a6f4-4d97-9992-297e783a4a50" />

### Steps to reproduce

1. Use code as above.
2. Attach GDScript to node in scene.
3. Run debug.

### Minimal reproduction project (MRP)

[dotnet-gdscript-constructor-mrp.zip](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/21546870/dotnet-gdscript-constructor-mrp.zip)
